It&#8217;s understood the bakkie the group was travelling in collided head on with a truck last night. JOHANNESBURG Seven people have been killed and another is critically injured following a collision on the R101 in Pienaars River in Limpopo.It s understood the bakkie the group was travelling in collided head on with a truck last night.The occupants of the heavy loaded truck escaped unharmed, while the driver of the bakkie has been transported to hospital in a critical condition.The police s Moathse Ngoepe says, Police are investigating a case of culpable homicide emanating from the death of seven people after a bakkie which was transporting these seven people and truck collided head-on, killing all seven people. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)